      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pain you're describing—starting near the belly button and moving to the lower right abdomen—is a classic sign of appendicitis, a medical emergency that requires immediate doctor attention. Do not take extra strength ibuprofen or opioids like oxycodone, as these can mask your symptoms and lead to dangerous delays in treatment. Since you mentioned needing sleep, you should prioritize getting to a hospital or urgent care facility immediately rather than trying to rest at home.",
